{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1120,"text":"I'd like you to imagine the world anew."},{"time":5840,"text":"I'd like to show you some maps,"},{"time":8039,"text":"which have been drawn by Ben Hennig,"},{"time":10800,"text":"of the planet in a way"},{"time":12520,"text":"that most of you will never\nhave seen the planet depicted before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18480,"text":"Here's an image\nthat you're very familiar with."},{"time":22480,"text":"I'm old enough that I was actually born\nbefore we saw this image."},{"time":26560,"text":"Apparently some of my first words\nwere \"moona, moona,\""},{"time":29160,"text":"but I think that's my mom\nhaving a particular fantasy"},{"time":32280,"text":"about what her baby boy could see"},{"time":34560,"text":"on the flickering\nblack and white TV screen."},{"time":39680,"text":"It's only been a few centuries"},{"time":41320,"text":"since we've actually, most of us,\nthought of our planet as spherical."},{"time":46160,"text":"When we first saw\nthese images in the 1960s,"},{"time":49240,"text":"the world was changing\nat an incredible rate."},{"time":54320,"text":"In my own little discipline\nof human geography,"},{"time":58600,"text":"a cartographer called Waldo Tobler"},{"time":61360,"text":"was drawing new maps of the planet,"},{"time":63920,"text":"and these maps have now spread,"},{"time":65440,"text":"and I'm going to show you one of them now."},{"time":68200,"text":"This map is a map of the world,"},{"time":71720,"text":"but it's a map which looks to you"},{"time":74160,"text":"a little bit strange."},{"time":76200,"text":"It's a map in which we stretched places,"},{"time":80040,"text":"so that those areas which contain\nmany people are drawn larger,"},{"time":84760,"text":"and those areas,\nlike the Sahara and the Himalayas,"},{"time":87720,"text":"in which there are few people,\nhave been shrunk away."},{"time":90760,"text":"Everybody on the planet\nis given an equal amount of space."},{"time":95120,"text":"The cities are shown shining bright."},{"time":98680,"text":"The lines are showing you\nsubmarine cables and trade routes."},{"time":102280,"text":"And there's one particular line\nthat goes from the Chinese port of Dalian"},{"time":105960,"text":"through past Singapore,"},{"time":107680,"text":"through the Suez Canal,"},{"time":109440,"text":"through the Mediterranean\nand round to Rotterdam."},{"time":111800,"text":"And it's showing you the route"},{"time":113320,"text":"of what was the world's\nlargest ship just a year ago,"},{"time":117280,"text":"a ship which was taking\nso many containers of goods"},{"time":123320,"text":"that when they were unloaded,"},{"time":125200,"text":"if the lorries had all gone in convoy,\nthey would have been 100 kilometers long."},{"time":130680,"text":"This is how our world is now connected."},{"time":133440,"text":"This is the quantity of stuff\nwe are now moving around the world,"},{"time":139440,"text":"just on one ship, on one voyage,"},{"time":142200,"text":"in five weeks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146320,"text":"We've lived in cities\nfor a very long time,"},{"time":149640,"text":"but most of us didn't live in cities."},{"time":151880,"text":"This is Çatalhöyük,\none of the world's first cities."},{"time":155040,"text":"At its peak 9,000 years ago,"},{"time":159160,"text":"people had to walk over the roofs\nof others' houses to get to their home."},{"time":166080,"text":"If you look carefully\nat the map of the city,"},{"time":169400,"text":"you'll see it has no streets,"},{"time":172280,"text":"because streets are something we invented."},{"time":175760,"text":"The world changes."},{"time":178000,"text":"It changes by trial and error."},{"time":181400,"text":"We work out slowly and gradually"},{"time":184320,"text":"how to live in better ways."},{"time":187480,"text":"And the world has changed\nincredibly quickly most recently."},{"time":193600,"text":"It's only within the last six,\nseven, or eight generations"},{"time":197560,"text":"that we have actually realized\nthat we are a species."},{"time":201840,"text":"It's only within the last few decades"},{"time":205240,"text":"that a map like this could be drawn."},{"time":210240,"text":"Again, the underlying map\nis the map of world population,"},{"time":215560,"text":"but over it, you're seeing arrows\nshowing how we spread out of Africa"},{"time":221240,"text":"with dates showing you\nwhere we think we arrived"},{"time":225040,"text":"at particular times."},{"time":227680,"text":"I have to redraw this map\nevery few months,"},{"time":231560,"text":"because somebody makes a discovery\nthat a particular date was wrong."},{"time":236560,"text":"We are learning about ourselves\nat an incredible speed."},{"time":243600,"text":"And we're changing."},{"time":246640,"text":"A lot of change is gradual."},{"time":248920,"text":"It's accretion."},{"time":250440,"text":"We don't notice the change"},{"time":253320,"text":"because we only have short lives,"},{"time":255160,"text":"70, 80, if you're lucky 90 years."},{"time":258560,"text":"This graph is showing you"},{"time":260600,"text":"the annual rate of population\ngrowth in the world."},{"time":264120,"text":"It was very low until around about 1850,"},{"time":268080,"text":"and then the rate of population growth"},{"time":270720,"text":"began to rise"},{"time":272840,"text":"so that around the time I was born,"},{"time":274880,"text":"when we first saw those images\nfrom the moon of our planet,"},{"time":280640,"text":"our global population\nwas growing at two percent a year."},{"time":285440,"text":"If it had carried on growing\nat two percent a year"},{"time":290600,"text":"for just another couple of centuries,"},{"time":294560,"text":"the entire planet would be covered"},{"time":296840,"text":"with a seething mass of human bodies"},{"time":299920,"text":"all touching each other."},{"time":303000,"text":"And people were scared."},{"time":304840,"text":"They were scared of population growth"},{"time":306680,"text":"and what they called\n\"the population bomb\" in 1968."},{"time":310040,"text":"But then, if you look\nat the end of the graph,"},{"time":313240,"text":"the growth began to slow."},{"time":316720,"text":"The decade --"},{"time":318120,"text":"the '70s, the '80s,\nthe '90s, the noughties,"},{"time":321600,"text":"and in this decade, even faster --"},{"time":324600,"text":"our population growth is slowing."},{"time":326240,"text":"Our planet is stabilizing."},{"time":327520,"text":"We are heading towards nine,\n10, or 11 billion people"},{"time":330560,"text":"by the end of the century."},{"time":332400,"text":"Within that change, you can see tumult."},{"time":335760,"text":"You can see the Second World War."},{"time":337600,"text":"You can see the pandemic\nin 1918 from influenza."},{"time":341800,"text":"You can see the great Chinese famine."},{"time":344400,"text":"These are the events\nwe tend to concentrate on."},{"time":346720,"text":"We tend to concentrate\non the terrible events in the news."},{"time":350680,"text":"We don't tend to concentrate\non the gradual change"},{"time":354360,"text":"and the good news stories."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357480,"text":"We worry about people."},{"time":359200,"text":"We worry about how many people there are."},{"time":361480,"text":"We worry about how you can\nget away from people."},{"time":365200,"text":"But this is the map of the world\nchanged again to make area large,"},{"time":369760,"text":"the further away\npeople are from each area."},{"time":374160,"text":"So if you want to know\nwhere to go to get away from everybody,"},{"time":378120,"text":"here's the best places to go."},{"time":380720,"text":"And every year, these areas get bigger,"},{"time":383560,"text":"because every year,\nwe are coming off the land globally."},{"time":386840,"text":"We are moving into the cities."},{"time":388320,"text":"We are packing in more densely."},{"time":390520,"text":"There are wolves again in Europe,"},{"time":392160,"text":"and the wolves are moving west\nacross the continent."},{"time":397200,"text":"Our world is changing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400920,"text":"You have worries."},{"time":403680,"text":"This is a map showing\nwhere the water falls on our planet."},{"time":408600,"text":"We now know that."},{"time":410320,"text":"And you can look at where Çatalhöyük was,"},{"time":414120,"text":"where three continents meet,\nAfrica, Asia, and Europe,"},{"time":416720,"text":"and you can see there are\na large number of people living there"},{"time":419720,"text":"in areas with very little water."},{"time":421320,"text":"And you can see areas in which\nthere is a great deal of rainfall as well."},{"time":425040,"text":"And we can get a bit more sophisticated."},{"time":428440,"text":"Instead of making\nthe map be shaped by people,"},{"time":431840,"text":"we can shape the map by water,"},{"time":434080,"text":"and then we can change it every month"},{"time":435960,"text":"to show the amount of water"},{"time":437640,"text":"falling on every small part of the globe."},{"time":441920,"text":"And you see the monsoons\nmoving around the planet,"},{"time":445240,"text":"and the planet almost appears\nto have a heartbeat."},{"time":449720,"text":"And all of this only became possible"},{"time":454920,"text":"within my lifetime"},{"time":456720,"text":"to see this is where we are living."},{"time":460640,"text":"We have enough water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463760,"text":"This is a map of where\nwe grow our food in the world."},{"time":469280,"text":"This is the areas that we will rely on\nmost for rice and maize and corn."},{"time":475760,"text":"People worry that there won't\nbe enough food, but we know,"},{"time":478640,"text":"if we just ate less meat\nand fed less of the crops to animals,"},{"time":483440,"text":"there is enough food for everybody"},{"time":485880,"text":"as long as we think of ourselves\nas one group of people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492120,"text":"And we also know"},{"time":495280,"text":"about what we do"},{"time":497360,"text":"so terribly badly nowadays."},{"time":501480,"text":"You will have seen this map\nof the world before."},{"time":507480,"text":"This is the map"},{"time":509440,"text":"produced by taking satellite images,"},{"time":512840,"text":"if you remember those satellites\naround the planet"},{"time":515640,"text":"in the very first slide I showed,"},{"time":519240,"text":"and producing an image\nof what the Earth looks like at night."},{"time":523720,"text":"When you normally see that map,"},{"time":525640,"text":"on a normal map, the kind of map\nthat most of you will be used to,"},{"time":530160,"text":"you think you are seeing\na map of where people live."},{"time":534120,"text":"Where the lights are shining up\nis where people live."},{"time":537320,"text":"But here, on this image of the world,"},{"time":541720,"text":"remember we've stretched the map again."},{"time":545320,"text":"Everywhere has the same density\nof people on this map."},{"time":550480,"text":"If an area doesn't have people,"},{"time":552680,"text":"we've shrunk it away"},{"time":554600,"text":"to make it disappear."},{"time":556160,"text":"So we're showing everybody"},{"time":558320,"text":"with equal prominence."},{"time":561320,"text":"Now, the lights no longer show you\nwhere people are,"},{"time":564640,"text":"because people are everywhere."},{"time":567120,"text":"Now the lights on the map,"},{"time":569080,"text":"the lights in London,\nthe lights in Cairo, the lights in Tokyo,"},{"time":572080,"text":"the lights on the Eastern Seaboard\nof the United States,"},{"time":575040,"text":"the lights show you where people live"},{"time":578000,"text":"who are so profligate with energy"},{"time":581160,"text":"that they can afford"},{"time":583680,"text":"to spend money"},{"time":585240,"text":"powering lights to shine up into the sky,"},{"time":588720,"text":"so satellites can draw an image like this."},{"time":592840,"text":"And the areas that are dark on the map"},{"time":595720,"text":"are either areas where people\ndo not have access to that much energy,"},{"time":600400,"text":"or areas where people do,"},{"time":602520,"text":"but they have learned to stop\nshining the light up into the sky."},{"time":607960,"text":"And if I could show you this map\nanimated over time,"},{"time":611520,"text":"you would see that Tokyo\nhas actually become darker,"},{"time":615120,"text":"because ever since the tsunami in Japan,"},{"time":618880,"text":"Japan has had to rely\non a quarter less electricity"},{"time":621320,"text":"because it turned\nthe nuclear power stations off."},{"time":625240,"text":"And the world didn't end."},{"time":627400,"text":"You just shone less light"},{"time":629600,"text":"up into the sky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633320,"text":"There are a huge number"},{"time":636320,"text":"of good news stories in the world."},{"time":639880,"text":"Infant mortality is falling"},{"time":643320,"text":"and has been falling\nat an incredible rate."},{"time":647920,"text":"A few years ago,"},{"time":650240,"text":"the number of babies dying\nin their first year of life in the world"},{"time":654200,"text":"fell by five percent in just one year."},{"time":659600,"text":"More children are going to school"},{"time":662120,"text":"and learning to read and write"},{"time":664760,"text":"and getting connected to the Internet"},{"time":667600,"text":"and going on to go to university"},{"time":670640,"text":"than ever before at an incredible rate,"},{"time":674560,"text":"and the highest number of young people\ngoing to university in the world"},{"time":680040,"text":"are women, not men."},{"time":683160,"text":"I can give you good news story\nafter good news story"},{"time":687080,"text":"about what is getting\nbetter in the planet,"},{"time":689720,"text":"but we tend to concentrate"},{"time":693880,"text":"on the bad news that is immediate."},{"time":696640,"text":"Rebecca Solnit, I think,\nput it brilliantly,"},{"time":701160,"text":"when she explained: \"The accretion\nof incremental, imperceptible changes"},{"time":706520,"text":"which can constitute progress\nand which render our era"},{"time":709360,"text":"dramatically different from the past\" --"},{"time":712200,"text":"the past was much more stable --"},{"time":715640,"text":"\"a contrast obscured by the undramatic\nnature of gradual transformation,"},{"time":720640,"text":"punctuated by occasional tumult.\""},{"time":724320,"text":"Occasionally, terrible things happen."},{"time":727440,"text":"You are shown those terrible things"},{"time":730200,"text":"on the news every night of the week."},{"time":733880,"text":"You are not told about\nthe population slowing down."},{"time":737880,"text":"You are not told about the world\nbecoming more connected."},{"time":740920,"text":"You are not told about the incredible\nimprovements in understanding."},{"time":744600,"text":"You are not told about\nhow we are learning to begin"},{"time":747760,"text":"to waste less and consume less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750240,"text":"This is my last map."},{"time":752360,"text":"On this map, we have taken the seas"},{"time":754760,"text":"and the oceans out."},{"time":757480,"text":"Now you are just looking"},{"time":759520,"text":"at about 7.4 billion people"},{"time":763400,"text":"with the map drawn\nin proportion to those people."},{"time":767240,"text":"You're looking at over a billion in China,"},{"time":769320,"text":"and you can see the largest\ncity in the world in China,"},{"time":772160,"text":"but you do not know its name."},{"time":775080,"text":"You can see that India"},{"time":776960,"text":"is in the center of this world."},{"time":779640,"text":"You can see that Europe is on the edge."},{"time":782960,"text":"And we in Exeter today"},{"time":786040,"text":"are on the far edge of the planet."},{"time":789000,"text":"We are on a tiny scrap of rock"},{"time":792000,"text":"off Europe"},{"time":793720,"text":"which contains less than one percent"},{"time":796360,"text":"of the world's adults,"},{"time":798400,"text":"and less than half a percent"},{"time":800960,"text":"of the world's children."},{"time":803640,"text":"We are living in a stabilizing world,\nan urbanizing world,"},{"time":808280,"text":"an aging world,"},{"time":810280,"text":"a connecting world."},{"time":812440,"text":"There are many, many things\nto be frightened about,"},{"time":816720,"text":"but there is no need for us\nto fear each other as much as we do,"},{"time":821960,"text":"and we need to see\nthat we are now living in a new world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826960,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828200,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}